I think there may be a problem with the number of functions in 64bit T3D. If someone can test this and confirm that would be great.  32 bit seems fine 

steps to recreate 

Use this function to make 300 extra functions

```
function genFunctions(%num){
    %fileWrite = new FileObject();
    %fileWrite.OpenForWrite("scripts/server/test.cs");
    for(%count = 0; %count < %num; %count++)
    {
        %fileWrite.writeLine("function test" @ %count @ "(){ echo(" @ "\"did it work\"" @");}"); 
    }
    %fileWrite.close();
}
```

exec the test.cs file in scripts/server/scriptExec.cs 
then load a mission 

As a side note if you do not exec it in the scriptsExec file and exec it in the console while in the mission it may crash randomly if not at all.
